messages.message:
Patch Set 3:

There are quite some other codes related to OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO. I think it might make sense to include all the flag handling codes into this single patch.

e.g.

# grep OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO lustre -r .
lustre/ptlrpc/wiretest.c:       LASSERTF(OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO == 0x800000ULL, "found 0x%.16llxULL\n",
lustre/ptlrpc/wiretest.c:                OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO);
lustre/include/uapi/linux/lustre/lustre_idl.h:#define OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO                   0x800000ULL /* PCC read-only */
lustre/include/uapi/linux/lustre/lustre_idl.h:                          OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO | \
lustre/llite/llite_lib.c:                                  OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO |
lustre/llite/pcc.c:     if (!(exp_connect_flags2(sbi->ll_md_exp) & OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO)) {
lustre/utils/wiretest.c:        LASSERTF(OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO == 0x800000ULL, "found 0x%.16llxULL\n",
lustre/utils/wiretest.c:                 OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO);
lustre/utils/wirecheck.c:       CHECK_DEFINE_64X(OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO);
./lustre/ptlrpc/wiretest.c:     LASSERTF(OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO == 0x800000ULL, "found 0x%.16llxULL\n",
./lustre/ptlrpc/wiretest.c:              OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO);
./lustre/include/uapi/linux/lustre/lustre_idl.h:#define OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO                 0x800000ULL /* PCC read-only */
./lustre/include/uapi/linux/lustre/lustre_idl.h:                                OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO | \
./lustre/llite/llite_lib.c:                                OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO |
./lustre/llite/pcc.c:   if (!(exp_connect_flags2(sbi->ll_md_exp) & OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO)) {
./lustre/utils/wiretest.c:      LASSERTF(OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO == 0x800000ULL, "found 0x%.16llxULL\n",
./lustre/utils/wiretest.c:               OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO);
./lustre/utils/wirecheck.c:     CHECK_DEFINE_64X(OBD_CONNECT2_PCCRO);
